-- Harper Says Canadians Want Careful Examination of Bids
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-11-20T19:35:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/harper-says-canadians-want-careful-examination-of-foreign-bids.html
Canadian Prime Minister  Stephen
Harper  said his government welcomes foreign investment and also
has an obligation to the public to give close scrutiny to
foreign takeover bids for domestic companies.  “We welcome foreign investment,” Harper said in response
to an opposition lawmaker’s question in the House of Commons
today in Ottawa. “Canadians expect us to examine these
investments carefully.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
